(96537, 'ruRU', 'Do you know of the Earthwarder, Neltharion? He was a glorious beast before he... fell. He was invulnerable to all but the gods in that age. Magnar worshipped him in his youth.\n\nEven though he was a venerated warrior Magnar wanted to be like him, invulnerable. His plan was arrogant. He would storm the nest of Neltharion himself and take something from his legendary hoard.\n\nMagnar and his warband fought Neltharion''s younglings in a fierce battle. They had just made the nest when the dragon returned. With one breath he wiped away entire force. Magnar grabbed one of his cast off scales, used it to shield himself, and was blown down the mountain.', '', 21154),
(96538, 'ruRU', 'So he left with nothing but a scale?', 'So he left with nothing but a scale?', 21154),
(96539, 'ruRU', 'Nothing but a scale? Hah! A scale from the most hard to kill dragon in the world!\n\nMagnar realized what he had and spent years learning the forge under masters both titanforged and vrykul. When he was finally skilled enough, he crafted from the scale a shield and sword that have never seen an equal. Those are the Armaments of the Black Wyrm. In the right hands they project the strength and invulnerability of the Earthwarder himself.\n\nTo this day I am still unsure if he was lucky to survive that encounter or if the Black Wyrm judged him worthy enough to live.', '', 21154),
