(111755, 'ruRU', '', '<A shadowy figure sits peacefully in the park, like a half-forgotten memory of a long-dead figure from the past. She seems to recognize your staff and greets you warmly, believing you to be someone else.>$b$bHello Alodi, old friend! Join me, would you? One of life''s most sublime pleasures is sitting in a park with a familiar old book.$b$bI think I shall plant a sapling here, so that in the years to come mages can sit beneath the shade of a small tree.', 21154),
(111756, 'ruRU', 'I heard the spy dislikes capes and refuses to wear one.', 'I heard the spy dislikes capes and refuses to wear one.', 21154),
(111757, 'ruRU', 'I heard that the spy left their cape in the palace before coming here.', 'I heard that the spy left their cape in the palace before coming here.', 21154),
(111758, 'ruRU', '', 'I will help if I must. You''ve concentrated so much power into that staff - I worry what will become of you!', 21154),
(111759, 'ruRU', '', 'If you desire I can take you where you back. I will return for Galford after Jotun has calmed down.', 21154),
(111760, 'ruRU', 'We are with you, champion. Let us end this beast!', '', 21154),
(111761, 'ruRU', '[TEMP] Let me tell you about my order and the Sparks of Tyr and the Silver Hand here.', '', 21154),
(111762, 'ruRU', '[TEMP] What''s this about the Tyr''s Guard? Who are you fools?', '[TEMP] What''s this about the Tyr''s Guard? Who are you fools?', 21154),
(111763, 'ruRU', '', '<A ghostly shade lingers in the citadel, a long-dead memory from Dalaran''s past. The slender figure recognizes your staff and mistakes you for someone else. She lazily looks you over through half-lidded eyes.>$b$bArchmage Alodi. You go to face Kathra''natir, then? The rest of the council ignores my warnings.$b$bVery well. I will not stop your suicide. If you seek to add my power to yours, you need only ask.$b$b<Fiora sips her wine, sadly, and does not look you in the eye.>', 21154),
(111764, 'ruRU', '', 'Very well. Make this count, mage.', 21154),
(111765, 'ruRU', '', 'The Legion has captured many of Stellagosa''s azure whelplings! Save them, so our allies in Azsuna may grow stronger!', 21154),
(111766, 'ruRU', '', 'It may seem small, but each whelp freed strengthens us against the legion. Well done!', 21154),
(111767, 'ruRU', '', 'Each Legion detachment is powered by souls. Cut them off from that power! Incapacitate that soul engine, and slay the Eredar that maintain it!', 21154),
(111768, 'ruRU', '', 'Outstanding! The soul engine should take some time to re-engage. You have bought us very valuable time.', 21154),
(111769, 'ruRU', '', 'Many of the Legion''s foul pets have flesh that reacts to mana. I hate to ask, but... could you fetch me some?', 21154),
(111770, 'ruRU', '', 'Legion spider eggs and a bunch of tendrils cut from their manastalkers should suffice.', 21154),
(111771, 'ruRU', '', 'Sometimes, I wish Garuhod''s writings called for slightly... cleaner reagents. Alas, these will do. Thank you.', 21154),
(111772, 'ruRU', 'So arrogant are the Legion that they defile my lands and think themselves safe.', '', 21154),
(111773, 'ruRU', 'You have made a statement to the Legion that they will be hunted anywhere they dare tread in Azsuna. Excellent work!', '', 21154),
(111774, 'ruRU', 'Strike them where they build their forces in Faronaar, and cripple them before they can move into greater Azsuna!', '', 21154),
(111775, 'ruRU', 'Day 20: Captured a new subject today. Number 16. He seems different somehow.', '', 21154),
(111776, 'ruRU', '<A half-remembered shadow lurks in the rear of the tavern, nosing through scrolls. The high-elf is a memory from another time. He recognizes your staff and greets you as an equal.>\n\nThe moment of truth arrives. Are you ready, Alodi? Are you certain that you can handle so much power?', '', 21154),
(111777, 'ruRU', 'Whoa... I didn''t expect the queen to show up... I''ll get you out of there. Hang on!', '', 21154),
(111778, 'ruRU', 'In time we must all face our demons. Better you than me.', '', 21154),
(111779, 'ruRU', '', '<A shadowy image of a gnome floats before you, a distant memory from the past. She is concentrating on a powerful spell, but mistakes you for someone else as you approach.>\n\nAlodi! You''ve returned. Let me see that staff of yours. Yes, yes... I can help you, of course. But you should hear what the rest of the council is saying behind your back. You''re lucky they need you.', 21154),
(111780, 'ruRU', 'Watch out!', '', 21154),
(111781, 'ruRU', 'Tick, tock!', '', 21154),
(111782, 'ruRU', '', 'I hope you know what you''re doing. But if not... At least we''re in for some fireworks. Good luck out there!', 21154),
(111783, 'ruRU', 'Portal coming up!', '', 21154),
(111784, 'ruRU', '', 'South gate! Another demon in the fields!', 21154),
(111785, 'ruRU', 'Your souls are so easily corrupted, mortals.', '', 21154),
(111786, 'ruRU', 'Gonna BASH you!', '', 21154),
(111787, 'ruRU', 'One heading for the wall to the northeast!', '', 21154),
(111788, 'ruRU', 'Today, we dealt a great blow to the unseen enemies of the Nightmare.', '', 21154),
(111789, 'ruRU', 'However, there remains a dire threat to the Emerald Dream. Xavius, Lord of the Nightmare, grows in power.', '', 21154),
(111790, 'ruRU', 'The true battle is only beginning. We must venture into the Nightmare itself, and defeat Xavius himself. Only then will Azeroth truly be safe.', '', 21154),
(111791, 'ruRU', 'This is perfectly safe! Oh, right... watch out for spiders down there. Whatever you do, don''t cut yourself down from the rope!', '', 21154),
(111792, 'ruRU', 'Take the gift of my blessing. Use my power to serve and protect the wilds.', '', 21154),
(111793, 'ruRU', 'Thank you, druids of the Dreamgrove. With $n at your helm, you are in capable hands.', '', 21154),
(111794, 'ruRU', 'Farewell.', '', 21154),
